claim.claim-text:
1. A method for manufacturing krill oil, the method comprising:
preparing krill;
adding protease to the krill and performing enzyme reaction;
extracting eicosapentaenoic acid, docosahexaenoic acid, phospholipids, and astaxanthin from the krill after performing the enzyme reaction; and
mixing the extracted eicosapentaenoic acid, docosahexaenoic acid, phospholipids, and astaxanthin,
wherein the protease comprises one or more chosen from serine alkaline proteases and metallo neutral proteases.
